## Security principles

📚 Topics Covered
✅ Task 2 — CIA Triad
Confidentiality: Ensuring data is accessible only to authorized users
Integrity: Maintaining data accuracy and trustworthiness
Availability: Ensuring systems and data are accessible when needed
✅ Task 3 — DAD Triad
Disclosure (opposite of Confidentiality)
Alteration (opposite of Integrity)
Denial (opposite of Availability)

Understanding attacker goals by reversing the CIA model.

✅ Task 4 — Fundamental Concepts of Security Models
Introduction to structured security frameworks
Understanding how policies enforce secure system behavior
Basics of models like access control and trust boundaries
✅ Task 5 — Defence-in-Depth
Layered security approach
Multiple defensive mechanisms across:
Network
System
Application
Reduces single points of failure
✅ Task 6 — ISO/IEC 19249
International standard for security architecture framework
Focus on:
Security design principles
System protection strategies
Risk-aware architecture
✅ Task 7 — Zero Trust vs Trust but Verify
Zero Trust:
Never trust, always verify
Continuous authentication and validation
Trust but Verify:
Trust established entities, but validate when needed
✅ Task 8 — Threat vs Risk
Threat: Potential cause of harm
Risk: Likelihood × Impact of a threat exploiting a vulnerability
🎯 Key Takeaways
Security is layered, not a single solution
Understanding attacker mindset is critical (DAD model)
Modern security relies heavily on Zero Trust principles
Risk management is central to decision-making
